{% extends "common/templates/layout.njk" %}
{% from "common/templates/macros/sub-navigation.njk" import subNavigation %}

{% block pageTitle %}
  Features - GOV.UK Pay
{% endblock %}

{% block beforeContent %}
  {{
    govukBreadcrumbs({
      items: [
        {
          text: "GOV.UK Services",
          href: "https://www.gov.uk/service-toolkit#gov-uk-services"
        },
        {
          text: "GOV.UK Pay",
          href: "https://www.payments.service.gov.uk/"
        },
        {
          text: "Features",
          href: "/features"
        }
      ]
    })
  }}
  {% include "common/templates/includes/flash.njk" %}
{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
<div class="govuk-grid-row">
  {{
    subNavigation([
      {
        name: 'Features',
        href: '/features',
        active: true
      },
      {
        name: 'Roadmap',
        href: '/roadmap'
      },
      {
        name: 'Security',
        href: '/security'
      },
      {
        name: 'GOV.UK Pay’s Payment Service Provider',
        href: '/payment-service-provider'
      },
      {
        name: 'Direct Debit on GOV.UK Pay',
        href: '/direct-debit'
      },
      {
        name: 'Payment links',
        href: '/payment-links'
      }
    ])
  }}

  <div class="govuk-grid-column-two-thirds">
    <h1 class="govuk-heading-l">Features</h1>
    <p class="govuk-body">You can use GOV.UK Pay to take online card payments.</p>
    <p class="govuk-body"><a class="govuk-link" href="https://selfservice.payments.service.gov.uk/login" data-click-events data-click-category="Content" data-click-action="External link clicked">Create a free test account</a> to get started. Once you’re ready to take payments, you’ll need to <a class="govuk-link" href="https://docs.payments.service.gov.uk/switching_to_live/#switching-to-live" data-click-events data-click-category="Content" data-click-action="External link clicked">make your account live<a/>.</p>
    <h2 class="govuk-heading-s">Card payments and payment links</h2>
    <p class="govuk-body">You can set up payment pages that look like your digital service to take credit and debit card payments.</p>
    <p class="govuk-body">If you do not have a digital service, or you do not want to use our API, you can use payment links instead.</p> 
    <p class="govuk-body">Payment links are pages on GOV.UK. They’re easy to set up and you can customise them with a friendly URL. Payment links are useful if you usually ask for payments by sending letters or emails.</p>
    <p class="govuk-body">Find out more about <a class="govuk-link" href="/payment-links" data-click-events data-click-category="Content" data-click-action="Internal link clicked">payment links.</a></p>

    <h2 class="govuk-heading-s">Free to use</h2>
    <p class="govuk-body">There are no costs for using GOV.UK Pay, but Payment Service Providers (<abbr title="payment service providers">PSPs</abbr>) will charge a transaction fee for payments.</p>

    <h2 class="govuk-heading-s">Take payments securely</h2>
    <p class="govuk-body">GOV.UK Pay complies with the Payment Card Industry Data Security Standard (PCI-DSS). We use established Payment Service Providers to process payments.</p>
    <p class="govuk-body">You can also choose to use 3D Secure authentication, such as Verified by Visa, to help prevent fraud.</p>

    <h2 class="govuk-heading-s">Choose your Payment Service Provider (PSP)</h2>
    <p class="govuk-body">You have 2 options.</p>
    
    <p class="govuk-body">GOV.UK Pay has already procured Stripe, as a Payment Service Provider for you.</p> 

    <p class="govuk-body">If you have your own PSP, GOV.UK Pay supports <abbr title="payment service providers">PSPs</abbr>:</p>
    <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
      <li>Worldpay Corporate Gateway</li>
      <li>Barclays ePDQ</li>
      <li>Barclays Smartpay/Adyen</li>
    </ul>

    <p class="govuk-body">You can use an existing contract, set up a new one, or switch <abbr title="payment service providers">PSPs</abbr> without additional technical work.</p>

    <h2 class="govuk-heading-s">Manage payments and reports</h2>
    <p class="govuk-body">GOV.UK Pay allows you to:</p>
    <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
      <li>check the status of transactions</li>
      <li>download transaction reports</li>
      <li>give full or partial refunds</li>
    </ul>

    <p class="govuk-body">You can also integrate your current income management systems with <a class="govuk-link" href="https://docs.payments.service.gov.uk/api_reference/#api-reference" data-click-events data-click-category="Content" data-click-action="External link clicked">our&nbsp;API</a>.</p>

    <h2 class="govuk-heading-s">Send emails to users</h2>  
    <p class="govuk-body">GOV.UK Pay can send emails to your users. For example, to confirm:</p>
    <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
      <li>payments</li>
      <li>refunds</li>
    </ul>

    <p class="govuk-body">Emails are sent using <a class="govuk-link" href="https://www.notifications.service.gov.uk/" data-click-events data-click-category="Content" data-click-action="External link clicked">GOV.UK Notify</a>.</p>

    <h2 class="govuk-heading-s">Manage your team</h2>
    <p class="govuk-body">Control what your team members can see and do. For example, you can:</p>
    <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
      <li>change permission levels for each team member</li>
      <li>invite new team members - including people without a government  email address</li>
      <li>remove users that have left your team</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="govuk-heading-s">Customise your branding</h2>
    <p class="govuk-body">Add your organisation’s branding to payment pages and emails instead of using the GOV.UK Pay logo.</p>

    <h2 class="govuk-heading-s">Welsh translations</h2>
    <p class="govuk-body"><a class="govuk-link" href="https://docs.payments.service.gov.uk/api_reference/#api-reference" data-click-events data-click-category="Content" data-click-action="External link clicked">Use the GOV.UK Pay API</a> to display Welsh translations of your payment pages.</p>
    <p class="govuk-body">You can also create <a class="govuk-link" href="https://www.payments.service.gov.uk/payment-links/" data-click-events data-click-category="Content" data-click-action="External link clicked"><a/> in Welsh.</p>

    <h2 class="govuk-heading-s">Use our API</h2>
    <p class="govuk-body">You can use our modern RESTful API for straightforward integration.</p> 
    <p class="govuk-body">Find out how to <a class="govuk-link" href="https://docs.payments.service.gov.uk/api_reference/#api-reference" data-click-events data-click-category="Content" data-click-action="External link clicked">integrate with GOV.UK Pay.</a></p>

    <h2 class="govuk-heading-s">Technical support</h2>
    <p class="govuk-body">GOV.UK Pay provides technical support from 9.30am to 5.30pm Monday to Friday. We also provide out-of-hours support for critical incidents.</p>

    <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">New features</h2>
    
    <h2 class="govuk-heading-s">Let users pay by Direct Debit</h2>
    <p class="govuk-body">GOV.UK Pay is introducing Direct Debit payments.</p> 
    <p class="govuk-body">You'll be able to set up Direct Debit mandates for regular, one-off or variable payments. GOV.UK Pay will verify users’ bank account details for you.</p> 
    <p class="govuk-body">We're looking for private beta partners. Get in touch at <a class="govuk-link" href="mailto:govuk-pay-support@digital.cabinet-office.gov.uk" data-click-events data-click-category="Content" data-click-action="Email link clicked">govuk-pay-support@digital.cabinet-office.gov.uk</a> if you can help.</p> 
    
    <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Queries and suggestions</h2>
    <p class="govuk-body">If you want to find out more about these features, or have some needs that GOV.UK Pay isn’t yet meeting, please get in touch with us by emailing <a class="govuk-link" href="mailto:govuk-pay-support@digital.cabinet-office.gov.uk" data-click-events data-click-category="Content" data-click-action="Email link clicked">govuk-pay-support@digital.cabinet-office.gov.uk</a> or chat with us in our <a class="govuk-link" href="https://ukgovernmentdigital.slack.com/messages/govuk-pay" data-click-events data-click-category="Content" data-click-action="External link clicked">cross-government Slack channel</a>.</p>
  </div>
</div>
{% endblock %}
